"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting the 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name' from the table 'defaultview-225'. It then creates a new column 'Immediate PT behavior' based on the values in the 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1', 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1', and 'Last PO Vendor Master Cash Discount Days 1' columns. If 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' is 0, it assigns the value 'Immediate PT on PO'. If 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' is not 0 and 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1' is 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT on Invoice but not on PO'. If 'Last PO Vendor Master Cash Discount Days 1' is 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT in Master Data'. If 'Last Inv. Item Cash Discount Days 1' is not 0 and 'Last PO Cash Discount Days 1' is 0, it assigns 'Immediate PT on PO but not on Invoice'. In all other cases, it assigns 'ok'. The query then counts the number of case_id's and names this column 'Number of Invoices'. It also sums the 'Inv. Converted USD Amount' and names this column 'Invoice Amounts'. The results are grouped by 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name' and 'Immediate PT behavior' and ordered by 'Number of Invoices' in descending order."
